President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their sadness over the passing of Dr. Margaret Burroughs. They praised her as an esteemed artist, historian, educator, and mentor, and acknowledged her contributions to American culture. In 1961, Dr. Burroughs founded the DuSable Museum of African-American History in Chicago, which became a renowned center for African-American history. She was also known for her generosity and commitment to underserved communities through her children's books, art workshops, and community centers. The Obamas extended their condolences to Dr. Burroughs' family and loved ones and stated that her legacy will continue to impact Chicago and the world.